how to run the project step by step:

1. Prerequisites
Make sure these are installed on your machine:
bash
docker --version        # Docker Desktop or Docker Engine
docker-compose --version
python --version        # Python 3.11+

2. enter the project
cd netflix-rec-system

3. Start all services
bash
docker-compose up --build
```
This spins up **MongoDB**, **Redis**, **FastAPI server**, and the **Change Stream listener** all at once. Wait until you see:
```
app | Models ready.

4. Seed data & train models (first time only)
Open a new terminal tab and run:
bash
docker-compose exec app python train.py
This will:

Seed 200 users, 500 movies, 10,000 interactions into MongoDB
Train the Neural CF model
Train the content-based model
Save models to saved_models/


5. Test the API
Get recommendations:
bash
curl http://localhost:8000/recommend/u1?last_item=m5&top_n=10
Force refresh (bypass cache):
bash
curl http://localhost:8000/recommend/u1?force_refresh=true
Health check:
bash
curl http://localhost:8000/health
```

Or open in browser:

http://localhost:8000/docs
FastAPI auto-generates an interactive Swagger UI where you can test all endpoints.

6. Stopping the project
bash
# Stop all containers
docker-compose down

# Stop and delete all data (MongoDB volume)
docker-compose down -v

